No fewer than one thousand children from different parts of Delta, Edo and Anambra States are billed to attend Regina Daniel’s Children’s Day carnival, holding at government field, Agbor in Ika South local government area of Delta tomorrow. The famous and young face of Nollywood, Daniel as gathered is prepared to dazzle the children, not only with classy entertainment laden with varied spices but with gifts in various sizes and qualities. The popular actress, who has lots of stories to tell regarding her childhood and acting career, as well as her stint in the box office as an adult, would be relating several visuals with reality. The event is supported by the Delta State government and Prince Ned Nwoko. Source: guardian